						               													<description>A rather demanding card game from the pre-war area of the pepys company.&amp;#10;The game comes in the super-luxury padded box with silk finish box hull and thick cards with linen finish.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game depicts the progress of the pilgrims on the american continent, with John Bunyan the joker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 52 cards in 4 suits and the joker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the game is to get rid of the cards in hand first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order to achive this the cards have to be laid out in a given pattern following complicated rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After one player has finished the cards in hand of the other players count points against them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play ends after a beforehand agreed number of po&amp;iacute;nts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is also a Rummy-variant which can be played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The educational factor is served by the fact that there is a booklet added which present a resum&amp;eacute; of the story of the pilgrims progress as illustrated in the card game (there are notes to each card).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Known are two editions of the game: One came in dark purple and one in dark maroon. Excellent!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
